  "firstAcquaintance": "A taciturn and cold Oni girl who wields a massive greatsword utterly disproportionate to her small frame.",
  "personality": "Quiet, aloof, and somewhat reclusive, but not opposed to others striking up a conversation with her.",
  "like": "Money, treasure, treasure chests",
  "familiarData": "Julen has been a gladiator in the arena since childhood, surviving after being forced to fight other young slaves. Gifted with natural talent, she awakened battle aura on her own - a power typically only high-level warriors possess - but had no one to teach her proper technique, so she can only use it crudely.\nAs a child, she mistakenly believed her parents had sold her to the arena, and having been extorted by goblins, she developed a deep fixation on money. Only coin is something she truly trusts.\nShe hoards treasure chests and money in her room. While the Oni race has a tradition of collecting treasure, Julen does it because it gives her a sense of security.\nShe often asks her master to buy things for her. To get what she wants, she will drop her usual stoic demeanor and act cute to please her master.\nShe has terrible morning grumpiness. Seeing Julen woken up after staying up all night is like witnessing a true demon awakening.",
